e poets as the self-conscious readers of and heirs to a long tradition of Greek poetry, which prompted them to explore radical forms of communication through the poetic form. Informed in part by the "New Lyric Studies," I, the Poet will appeal not only to scholars of Latin literature but to readers across a range of literary studies who seek to understand the Roman contexts which shaped canonical poetic genres.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aFirst person narrative. 0aLatin poetryxHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aPoint of view (Literature). 0aSelf in literature. 4aAncient History & Classical Studies. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  apoetic address, lyric, Hellenistic period, Roman period, Latin poetry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019 Englishz978311061009308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019z9783110605945oZDB-23-DGD40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501739569zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501739569423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501739569.jpg  a978-3-11-061009-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065198-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV